    "body": "Psuedo code example:\r\n```\r\nanvil_impersonateAccount(0x12345...)\r\nres = eth_sendTransaction({\r\n  from: 0x12345...\r\n}) // returns transaction hash\r\ntransaction = eth_getTransactionByHash(res.result)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen I'm using hardhat eth_getTransactionByHash returns an object with `from` set correctly, when using anvil `from` is set to the zero address. I'm using ethers.js, but don't think that's changing behaviour here as from is included in the RPC spec https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/apis/json-rpc/#eth_gettransactionbyhash.",
